SERVICES
1. What is systemd and why is it used?
A: its used to start and manage services and also boot processes.

2. How do you check if a service is running in production?
A: systemctl status service_name

3. How do you restart a failed service in production?
A: systemctl restart service_name

4. A service is failing to start, what do you do?
A: check service status: systemctl status service_name
   check logs: journalctl -u app -xe
   check config file: nginx -t
   check port conflict: ss -tulpn | grep 80

5. Difference between start, enable, reload, restart?
A: start --> starts the service
   enable --> start at boot
   reload --> refresh without downtime
   restart --> stop+start

6. how do you create a custom systemd service?
A: Example:
     Bash:
       sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/myapp.service
     Inside file:
        [Unit]
        Description=My App Service
        After=network.target
        
        [Service]
        ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /home/ubuntu/app.py
        Restart=always
        User=ubuntu
        
        [Install]
        WantedBy=multi-user.target
    Then:
        systemctl daemon-reload
        systemctl start myapp
        systemctl enable myapp

NETWORKING
7. How do you check if a server has internet connectivity?
A:    ping 8.8.8.8
      curl google.com 

8. How do you check open ports in linux?
A:   ss -tulpn
     netstat -tulpn
     lsof -i

9. Diff between port 80,443?
A:80 --> HTTP --> not secure
  443 --> HTTPS --> secure as its encrypted

10. A web app is not accessible, what do you check?
A: check service : systemctl status nginx
   check port: ss -tulpn | grep 80
   check firewall / security group
   check logs: tail -f /var/logs/nginx/error.log

11. What is DNS resolution issue?
A: Ping IP works but Ping domain fails due to wrong DNS Server

12. Diff between TCP and UDP?
A: TCP --> reliable, connection-based, used in web apps
   UDP --> fast but no guarantee, connection-less, used in streaming, gaming

13. What is local host vs 0.0.0.0
A: local host --> local machine 
   0.0.0.0 --> all network interfaces (public access)

14. Production incident: API is slow but server is working
A: check cpu memory: free -m
   top

15. What is SSH Tunneling?
A: used to securily access remote servers

16. how do you check routing issues?
A: ip route

17. Prodiction scenario : firewall blocking traffic
A: in aws --> check security group
   in local machine in ufw is enabled --> ufw status --> if you want to allow any : ufw allow 80

18. Website is up but users cannot access it, why?
A: check firewall, DNS issue, check security group, load balancer misconfig, SSL expired

19. Service works locally but not from browser, why?
A: not set to 0.0.0.0
   port not exposed
   firewall blocking
 
